---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" sideBarActiveItemID="about">
  <div class="pb-12 mt-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">About</div>
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>
        I'm Ken Rhodes, a retired software developer and small business owner
        based in Saint Paul, Minnesota.
        I build open-source tools for communities, with a focus on civic engagement
        and local coordination.
      </p>
      <p>
        I use Claude Code during development, and I've adopted the guidance provided
        by Linus Torvalds and the Linux kernel maintainers for AI-assisted code
        contributions, adapted for my MIT-licensed projects:
        <ul>
          <li>All code must be compatible with the MIT license only</li>
          <li>
             AI agents can't sign off on code contributions. The human contributor
             is responsible for:
             <ul>
                <li>Reviewing all AI-generated code</li>
                <li>Ensuring compliance with licensing requirements</li>
                <li>Taking full responsibility for the contribution</li>
             </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
             All AI-assisted contributions must contain an Assisted-by tag in
             the following format: Assisted by: AGENT_NAME:MODEL_VERSION
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        All of my projects are open source under the MIT license. If you're working
        on something similar or want to deploy one of these tools in your community,
        get in touch.
      </p>

      <h3>Elsewhere</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://bsky.app/profile/knrhds.com" target="_blank">BlueSky (@knrhds.com)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/keenrodent" target="_blank">GitHub (keenrodent)</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Contact</h3>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:k@knrhds.com">k@knrhds.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
